Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.67,0:01:00.80,1080CN UP,,0,0,0,,左侧为正确打磨的镜子 右侧为出现球面像差的镜子
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.93,0:02:46.17,1080CN UP,,0,0,0,,invariability，不变性
Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.17,0:00:04.72,1080CN,,0,0,0,,1990年四月，美国的发现号航天飞机升空
Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.17,0:00:04.72,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In April of 1990 the American space shuttle Discovery launched up from the Earth
Dialogue: 1,0:00:04.86,0:00:11.56,1080CN,,0,0,0,,将哈勃太空望远镜送到航天飞机从未到达过的高度
Dialogue: 2,0:00:04.86,0:00:11.56,1080EN,,0,0,0,,into a higher orbit than ever before to deploy a special payload the Hubble Space Telescope
Dialogue: 1,0:00:11.85,0:00:14.36,1080CN,,0,0,0,,那个高度，大气层几乎是最稀薄的
Dialogue: 2,0:00:11.85,0:00:14.36,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Above even the thinnest parts of the atmosphere
Dialogue: 1,0:00:14.43,0:00:18.08,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这使得哈勃能够清晰地看到遥远的恒星与星系
Dialogue: 2,0:00:14.43,0:00:18.08,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Hubble would be able to see far-off stars and galaxies without distortion
Dialogue: 1,0:00:18.25,0:00:21.79,1080CN,,0,0,0,,让我们能看到宇宙更遥远的过去
Dialogue: 2,0:00:18.25,0:00:21.79,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and expand our understanding of the distant past
Dialogue: 1,0:00:22.14,0:00:24.32,1080CN,,0,0,0,,至少原计划是这样
Dialogue: 2,0:00:22.14,0:00:24.32,1080EN,,0,0,0,,or at least that was the plan
Dialogue: 1,0:00:24.49,0:00:28.04,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但到了六月，人们证实哈勃出现了大问题
Dialogue: 2,0:00:24.49,0:00:28.04,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But by June it was clear there was something a very wrong
Dialogue: 1,0:00:28.52,0:00:33.61,1080CN,,0,0,165,,望远镜的主镜竟然无法准确对焦
Dialogue: 2,0:00:28.52,0:00:33.61,1080EN,,0,0,130,,The telescope with one of the most perfectly round mirrors couldn't focus properly
Dialogue: 1,0:00:33.88,0:00:38.36,1080CN,,0,0,0,,太空中首个最先进的宇宙观测平台成了近视眼
Dialogue: 2,0:00:33.88,0:00:38.36,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Apparently the first great space observatory was short sighted
Dialogue: 1,0:00:38.89,0:00:45.44,1080CN,,0,0,0,,哈勃直径2.5米(8英尺2英寸)的主镜形状出现了偏差
Dialogue: 2,0:00:38.89,0:00:45.44,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Hubble's two and a half meter or 8'2" foot mirror was rendered incapable by an error in its shape
Dialogue: 1,0:00:45.48,0:00:48.49,1080CN,,0,0,0,,偏差大概是头发直径的五分之一(2.2微米)
Dialogue: 2,0:00:45.48,0:00:48.49,1080EN,,0,0,0,,less than one fiftieth of the width of a human hair
Dialogue: 1,0:00:48.97,0:00:53.10,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这个偏差术语叫“球面像差”
Dialogue: 2,0:00:48.97,0:00:53.10,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The primary mirror suffered from what is known as spherical aberration
Dialogue: 1,0:00:53.37,0:00:57.44,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这在业余爱好者制造的简易望远镜中很常见
Dialogue: 2,0:00:53.37,0:00:57.44,1080EN,,0,0,0,,more often found in sloppily made amateur telescope projects
Dialogue: 1,0:00:57.74,0:01:00.40,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但不应该出现在造价上百万美元的太空望远镜上
Dialogue: 2,0:00:57.74,0:01:00.40,1080EN,,0,0,0,,not multi-million dollar space telescopes
Dialogue: 1,0:01:01.29,0:01:04.89,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但这个偏差在主镜制造中存在了整整十年
Dialogue: 2,0:01:01.29,0:01:04.89,1080EN,,0,0,0,,However this was a problem almost a decade in the making
Dialogue: 1,0:01:04.89,0:01:12.09,1080CN,,0,0,0,,NASA找珀金埃尔默公司制造哈勃望远镜的光学组件与精确制导系统
Dialogue: 2,0:01:04.89,0:01:12.09,1080EN,,0,0,0,,NASA had contracted the private firm Perkin-Elmer to make Hubble's optical assembly and the fine guidance system
Dialogue: 1,0:01:12.62,0:01:17.68,1080CN,,0,0,0,,主镜的制造开始于1979年，完成于1981年
Dialogue: 2,0:01:12.62,0:01:17.68,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Construction of the primary mirror began in 1979 and was completed in 1981
Dialogue: 1,0:01:18.14,0:01:21.28,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但其间整个项目其实如履薄冰
Dialogue: 2,0:01:18.14,0:01:21.28,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but during these years the whole project was under threat
Dialogue: 1,0:01:21.58,0:01:25.07,1080CN,,0,0,0,,经费爆炸，交付日期各种咕
Dialogue: 2,0:01:21.58,0:01:25.07,1080EN,,0,0,0,,costs were rising and the scheduled to deliver on time was slipping
Dialogue: 1,0:01:25.52,0:01:31.72,1080CN,,0,0,0,,甲方爸爸NASA逼迫珀金埃尔默公司，要么抓紧干要么滚犊子
Dialogue: 2,0:01:25.52,0:01:31.72,1080EN,,0,0,0,,NASA put the heat on the management of Perkin-Elmer pushing them to keep up with the schedule or loose for contract
Dialogue: 1,0:01:32.09,0:01:36.52,1080CN,,0,0,0,,在幕后，主镜的打磨与测试也在进行中
Dialogue: 2,0:01:32.09,0:01:36.52,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Behind-the-scenes, the polishing and testing of the primary mirror was underway
Dialogue: 1,0:01:36.96,0:01:39.85,1080CN,,0,0,0,,由于哈勃的镜面是非球面的
Dialogue: 2,0:01:36.96,0:01:39.85,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Because Hubble's mirror was an aspherical design
Dialogue: 1,0:01:39.85,0:01:44.88,1080CN,,0,0,0,,因此需要一种叫“零校正器”的特殊仪器来精确检查打磨质量
Dialogue: 2,0:01:39.85,0:01:44.88,1080EN,,0,0,0,,it required special apparatus to check its quality known as a null corrector
Dialogue: 1,0:01:45.44,0:01:52.38,1080CN,,0,0,145,,为此，珀金埃尔默还自制了一台高精零校正器(RNC)
Dialogue: 2,0:01:45.44,0:01:52.38,1080EN,,0,0,110,,Perkin-Elmer even designed their own high specification reflective null corrector or RNC
Dialogue: 1,0:01:52.64,0:02:01.26,1080CN,,0,0,145,,测试标准可达一微米(千分之一毫米)，以满足太空望远镜的精度需求
Dialogue: 2,0:01:52.64,0:02:01.26,1080EN,,0,0,110,,to test the exact standard of one micrometer or 1/1000 of a millimeter as required for the Space Telescope
Dialogue: 1,0:02:02.08,0:02:09.74,1080CN,,0,0,0,,RNC呈圆柱体，76厘米(2.5英尺)高，半米宽(1.5英尺)
Dialogue: 2,0:02:02.08,0:02:09.74,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The RNC was a cylinder, 76 centimeters, 2.5 feet high and about half a meter or 1.5 feet wide
Dialogue: 1,0:02:10.16,0:02:13.42,1080CN,,0,0,0,,其内部，两面镜子和一块透镜被安排的明明白白
Dialogue: 2,0:02:10.16,0:02:13.42,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Inside, two mirrors and a lens were arranged
Dialogue: 1,0:02:13.42,0:02:17.15,1080CN,,0,0,0,,从而制造波阵面，射向下方的哈勃主镜
Dialogue: 2,0:02:13.42,0:02:17.15,1080EN,,0,0,0,,to create a wavefront on the Hubble primary mirror below
Dialogue: 1,0:02:17.71,0:02:23.20,1080CN,,0,0,145,,如果主镜打磨正确，得到的应该是左图没有外轮廓的线条
Dialogue: 2,0:02:17.71,0:02:23.20,1080EN,,0,0,110,,If the mirror was fabricated perfectly, this wavefront would show no contour lines
Dialogue: 1,0:02:23.40,0:02:25.52,1080CN,,0,0,145,,“‘零’校正器”因此得名
Dialogue: 2,0:02:23.40,0:02:25.52,1080EN,,0,0,110,,hence the a null in the instruments name
Dialogue: 1,0:02:25.96,0:02:32.46,1080CN,,0,0,165,,该设备得到认可后，人们花了两周把它放在特制房间内的一个塔顶上
Dialogue: 2,0:02:25.96,0:02:32.46,1080EN,,0,0,130,,The apparatus was approved and set up on a tower in a dedicated room, a process that took two weeks
Dialogue: 1,0:02:32.96,0:02:36.48,1080CN,,0,0,155,,RNC的位置由一根因瓦合金棒测量得到
Dialogue: 2,0:02:32.96,0:02:36.48,1080EN,,0,0,120,,The position of the RNC's lens was measured by an Invar Rod
Dialogue: 1,0:02:36.89,0:02:42.48,1080CN,,0,0,155,,该测量棒由镍钢合金组成，膨胀系数随温度变化极小，得名“不变钢”
Dialogue: 2,0:02:36.89,0:02:42.48,1080EN,,0,0,120,,a precision made and measured rod of nickel iron alloy named for its invariability
Dialogue: 1,0:02:42.48,0:02:46.16,1080CN,,0,0,155,,该测量棒由镍钢合金组成，膨胀系数随温度变化极小，得名“不变钢”
Dialogue: 2,0:02:42.48,0:02:46.16,1080EN,,0,0,120,,specifically low expansion under different temperatures
Dialogue: 1,0:02:46.59,0:02:52.12,1080CN,,0,0,155,,如果测量棒长度改变不到一毫米，测量结果也会出错
Dialogue: 2,0:02:46.59,0:02:52.12,1080EN,,0,0,120,,If the length of this rod varied by even a fraction of a millimeter the test measurements would be wrong
Dialogue: 1,0:02:52.24,0:02:54.70,1080CN,,0,0,155,,从而导致主镜打磨出现偏差
Dialogue: 2,0:02:52.24,0:02:54.70,1080EN,,0,0,120,,and the mirror would be ground to a wrong shape
Dialogue: 1,0:02:55.36,0:03:01.16,1080CN,,0,0,0,,当技术人员降低RNC中的透镜时，他们发现根本装不进去
Dialogue: 2,0:02:55.36,0:03:01.16,1080EN,,0,0,0,,As the technicians lowered the lens of the RNC into position, they noticed they couldn't get it all to fit together
Dialogue: 1,0:03:01.48,0:03:05.04,1080CN,,0,0,0,,测量棒长了一毫米多
Dialogue: 2,0:03:01.48,0:03:05.04,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The Invar Rod stuck out by just over a millimeter
Dialogue: 1,0:03:05.61,0:03:09.15,1080CN,,0,0,0,,测量棒的两端是打磨过的弧面
Dialogue: 2,0:03:05.61,0:03:09.15,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The ends of the Invar rod were rounded and polished
Dialogue: 1,0:03:09.34,0:03:14.56,1080CN,,0,0,0,,因为定位系统使用的是光干涉测量而不是机械测量
Dialogue: 2,0:03:09.34,0:03:14.56,1080EN,,0,0,0,,because the positioning system used a light interferometer rather than a mechanical measurement
Dialogue: 1,0:03:15.00,0:03:20.25,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这个过程中需要一束会聚光在测量棒末端反射回来
Dialogue: 2,0:03:15.00,0:03:20.25,1080EN,,0,0,0,,As part of this process a focused beam of light was reflected off the end of the Invar rod
Dialogue: 1,0:03:20.62,0:03:24.33,1080CN,,0,0,0,,为了保证会聚光刚好在测量棒末端中心反射
Dialogue: 2,0:03:20.62,0:03:24.33,1080EN,,0,0,0,,To make sure that it was focused exactly on the center of a rod end
Dialogue: 1,0:03:24.54,0:03:28.35,1080CN,,0,0,0,,测量棒两端各装有一个适配帽
Dialogue: 2,0:03:24.54,0:03:28.35,1080EN,,0,0,0,,field caps were fitted to hold the rods in position laterally
Dialogue: 1,0:03:28.75,0:03:34.20,1080CN,,0,0,0,,其中间有小孔，保证会聚光能刚好射在测量棒末端中心处
Dialogue: 2,0:03:28.75,0:03:34.20,1080EN,,0,0,0,,these caps had a hole in the center to allow the focus beams hit the rod end
Dialogue: 1,0:03:34.40,0:03:37.13,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而适配帽一圈则是不反光的
Dialogue: 2,0:03:34.40,0:03:37.13,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and a non-reflective surface coating around it
Dialogue: 1,0:03:37.72,0:03:42.38,1080CN,,0,0,145,,在某一时刻，其中一个适配帽上不反光的部分
Dialogue: 2,0:03:37.72,0:03:42.38,1080EN,,0,0,110,,At some point, a small section of this non-reflective coating
Dialogue: 1,0:03:42.38,0:03:46.83,1080CN,,0,0,145,,从中间剥落了一小块
Dialogue: 2,0:03:42.38,0:03:46.83,1080EN,,0,0,110,,on one of the field caps was chipped off around the center hole
Dialogue: 1,0:03:47.32,0:03:50.62,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而技术人员设定会聚光位置时
Dialogue: 2,0:03:47.32,0:03:50.62,1080EN,,0,0,0,,When the technician was setting up the focused beam
Dialogue: 1,0:03:50.99,0:03:57.34,1080CN,,0,0,0,,他得到的是适配帽上剥落部分的反射光线
Dialogue: 2,0:03:50.99,0:03:57.34,1080EN,,0,0,0,,he got a reflection from the chipped area of the endcap instead of the rod end
Dialogue: 1,0:03:57.72,0:04:02.57,1080CN,,0,0,0,,造成测量棒位置出现1.3毫米的误差
Dialogue: 2,0:03:57.72,0:04:02.57,1080EN,,0,0,0,,which caused a 1.3 millimeter misplacing of the Invar rod
Dialogue: 1,0:04:03.08,0:04:07.87,1080CN,,0,0,0,,他们没有花时间调查RNC组装后和测量棒不适配
Dialogue: 2,0:04:03.08,0:04:07.87,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Rather than wasting time investigating why the assembly didn't match the Invar Rod
Dialogue: 1,0:04:08.14,0:04:13.96,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而是找三个垫圈硬塞进支架里去支撑透镜
Dialogue: 2,0:04:08.14,0:04:13.96,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the crew found three metal spacers and squeezed them into the bracket holding the lens
Dialogue: 1,0:04:14.20,0:04:16.67,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这样测量棒就能塞进去啦~
Dialogue: 2,0:04:14.20,0:04:16.67,1080EN,,0,0,0,,so now it agreed with the measuring rod
Dialogue: 1,0:04:17.28,0:04:23.47,1080CN,,0,0,0,,然后RNC就再没动过，防止干扰到主镜的微调
Dialogue: 2,0:04:17.28,0:04:23.47,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Then the RNC was left in place so as not to disturb its supposedly fine calibration
Dialogue: 1,0:04:23.79,0:04:29.39,1080CN,,0,0,0,,RNC组装上的疏忽导致主镜打磨精确度出现问题
Dialogue: 2,0:04:23.79,0:04:29.39,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The result of this oversight in the assembly of the RNC would lead to the mirror being precisely polished
Dialogue: 1,0:04:29.95,0:04:34.27,1080CN,,0,0,0,,其误差超过了容忍限度的十倍
Dialogue: 2,0:04:29.95,0:04:34.27,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but with an error ten times greater than the specified tolerance
Dialogue: 1,0:04:34.86,0:04:38.19,1080CN,,0,0,0,,就这样，整个团队花了九个月打磨主镜
Dialogue: 2,0:04:34.86,0:04:38.19,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Every day for 9 months the crew polished the primary mirror
Dialogue: 1,0:04:38.32,0:04:43.77,1080CN,,0,0,0,,定期把主镜送到零校正器下观察还要打磨多久
Dialogue: 2,0:04:38.32,0:04:43.77,1080EN,,0,0,0,,periodically moving it on its tracks to the null corrector to see how much closer they were to the final shape
Dialogue: 1,0:04:44.22,0:04:48.75,1080CN,,0,0,0,,最终RNC给出了刚刚提到的“零”的结果
Dialogue: 2,0:04:44.22,0:04:48.75,1080EN,,0,0,0,,At the end of the long process the RNC gave a Null result
Dialogue: 1,0:04:48.92,0:04:52.43,1080CN,,0,0,0,,于是这块主镜就被打磨到“完美”了
Dialogue: 2,0:04:48.92,0:04:52.43,1080EN,,0,0,0,,at last the so-called perfect mirror was finished
Dialogue: 1,0:04:53.07,0:04:59.77,1080CN,,0,0,0,,为了测试主镜形状，他们还用另外一个简易的零校正器
Dialogue: 2,0:04:53.07,0:04:59.77,1080EN,,0,0,0,,To verify the mirror shape another test was carried out using a cruder refractive Null corrector
Dialogue: 1,0:05:00.17,0:05:02.81,1080CN,,0,0,0,,却给出了不同的结果
Dialogue: 2,0:05:00.17,0:05:02.81,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but this test gave a different result
Dialogue: 1,0:05:03.02,0:05:07.39,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这次测试尽管显示哈勃主镜有缺陷
Dialogue: 2,0:05:03.02,0:05:07.39,1080EN,,0,0,0,,This time it appears as though the Hubble's mirror had a flaw
Dialogue: 1,0:05:08.00,0:05:15.02,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但测试用的零校正器并没有经过球面像差测试
Dialogue: 2,0:05:08.00,0:05:15.02,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But as the refractive null corrector had not been certified for testing against spherical aberration
Dialogue: 1,0:05:15.45,0:05:17.20,1080CN,,0,0,0,,于是人们并没有在意这个结果
Dialogue: 2,0:05:15.45,0:05:17.20,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the result was discounted
Dialogue: 1,0:05:17.37,0:05:21.10,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以结果是，主镜的误差其实早就被发现了，但没人在意
Dialogue: 2,0:05:17.37,0:05:21.10,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The fault had been found but it had been ignored
Dialogue: 1,0:05:21.31,0:05:26.25,1080CN,,0,0,0,,更惨的是，人们没有深入调查这两次测试结果上的出入
Dialogue: 2,0:05:21.31,0:05:26.25,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and moreover the discrepancy between the two tests had not been investigated further
Dialogue: 1,0:05:26.35,0:05:31.74,1080CN,,0,0,0,,也没人在维修记录上提到之前说的三个垫圈
Dialogue: 2,0:05:26.35,0:05:31.74,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and the written documentation of the fix with the spacers was also misplaced
Dialogue: 1,0:05:32.48,0:05:37.29,1080CN,,0,0,0,,后来挑战者号航天飞机出事，任务延期，镜面封存了四年
Dialogue: 2,0:05:32.48,0:05:37.29,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Over the four years that the mirror was stored due to delays because of the Challenger shuttle disaster
Dialogue: 1,0:05:37.40,0:05:42.47,1080CN,,0,0,0,,几个大学要求拿出来亲自测试一下主镜，但不了了之
Dialogue: 2,0:05:37.40,0:05:42.47,1080EN,,0,0,0,,several universities requested permission to test the mirror and all were turned down
Dialogue: 1,0:05:42.47,0:05:48.03,1080CN,,0,0,0,,因为制造商珀金埃尔默对他们自己的测试过程蜜汁自信
Dialogue: 2,0:05:42.47,0:05:48.03,1080EN,,0,0,0,,because the manufacturers were confident about their own testing procedures
Dialogue: 1,0:05:48.40,0:05:55.12,1080CN,,0,0,0,,于是十年后，这架造价15亿美元的太空望远镜就这样带病上天了
Dialogue: 2,0:05:48.40,0:05:55.12,1080EN,,0,0,0,,A decade later the one and a half billion dollar Space Telescope was high above the earth with a flawed mirror
Dialogue: 1,0:05:56.16,0:05:59.98,1080CN,,0,0,155,,柯达那边其实有一个完美的备份主镜
Dialogue: 2,0:05:56.16,0:05:59.98,1080EN,,0,0,120,,There was a perfect backup mirror that had been made by Kodak
Dialogue: 1,0:06:00.40,0:06:03.52,1080CN,,0,0,155,,但望远镜已经上天，不可能在轨更换主镜
Dialogue: 2,0:06:00.40,0:06:03.52,1080EN,,0,0,120,,but it would have been impossible to replace the mirror once in orbit
Dialogue: 1,0:06:03.71,0:06:09.44,1080CN,,0,0,0,,把它运回地球重装也太浪费时间浪费钱
Dialogue: 2,0:06:03.71,0:06:09.44,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and too time-consuming and expensive to bring the Hubble back to earth of refitting
Dialogue: 1,0:06:10.20,0:06:15.71,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以在199{\fs52}3年，人们执行了一次伟大而昂贵的航天飞机任务，其间进行五次太空行走
Dialogue: 2,0:06:10.20,0:06:15.71,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So in 1993, an ambitious and expensive shuttle mission with five spacewalks
Dialogue: 1,0:06:16.03,0:06:20.27,1080CN,,0,0,0,,将修正用的光学组件安装在哈勃的副镜上，成功解决了问题
Dialogue: 2,0:06:16.03,0:06:20.27,1080EN,,0,0,0,,managed to install corrective optics on the secondary mirror to fix the problem
Dialogue: 1,0:06:20.89,0:06:24.35,1080CN,,0,0,0,,当哈勃的问题发现以后
Dialogue: 2,0:06:20.89,0:06:24.35,1080EN,,0,0,0,,When the cause of Hubble's trouble was eventually found
Dialogue: 1,0:06:24.68,0:06:29.13,1080CN,,0,0,0,,珀金埃尔默同意支付1500万美元罚金
Dialogue: 2,0:06:24.68,0:06:29.13,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Perkin-Elmer agreed to pay a fine of $15 million dollars
Dialogue: 1,0:06:29.55,0:06:32.35,1080CN,,0,0,0,,以此来避免政府进一步的起诉
Dialogue: 2,0:06:29.55,0:06:32.35,1080EN,,0,0,0,,thereby avoiding a lawsuit by the government
Dialogue: 1,0:06:32.89,0:06:38.41,1080CN,,0,0,0,,珀金埃尔默和NASA也因对制造过程的品控的不负责
Dialogue: 2,0:06:32.89,0:06:38.41,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Both Perkin-Elmer and NASA were heavily criticised for not picking up on the quality control issues
Dialogue: 1,0:06:38.56,0:06:41.96,1080CN,,0,0,0,,和依靠单一设备进行测试的行为而被批判一番
Dialogue: 2,0:06:38.56,0:06:41.96,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and relying upon a single test instrument
Dialogue: 1,0:06:42.35,0:06:46.21,1080CN,,0,0,0,,哈勃至今仍在服役，几十年中维护了几次
Dialogue: 2,0:06:42.35,0:06:46.21,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Hubble is still in operation today and has been updated over the years
Dialogue: 1,0:06:46.48,0:06:51.77,1080CN,,0,0,175,,预计会继续服役到2028到2040年
Dialogue: 2,0:06:46.48,0:06:51.77,1080EN,,0,0,140,,And it's expected that it will be in operation until between 2028 and 2040
Dialogue: 1,0:06:52.14,0:06:59.40,1080CN,,0,0,175,,如果再没其它飞行器给它加燃料续命，大气阻力会让它落回地球
Dialogue: 2,0:06:52.14,0:06:59.40,1080EN,,0,0,140,,when the natural decay its orbits will bring it back to earth if it is not reboosted into a higher orbit
Dialogue: 1,0:06:59.84,0:07:02.80,1080CN,,0,0,165,,在那之前它仍会给人类带来
Dialogue: 2,0:06:59.84,0:07:02.80,1080EN,,0,0,130,,Until then it will continue to provide mankind with
Dialogue: 1,0:07:02.80,0:07:08.97,1080CN,,0,0,165,,无数既有科学价值、又美轮美奂的宇宙图片
Dialogue: 2,0:07:02.80,0:07:08.97,1080EN,,0,0,130,,some of the most scientifically useful and inspirational views of our universe to date
